comment_data.body: @iphydf @nurupo @grayhatter [You wrote and pushed these lines](https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore/blame/master/toxcore/tox.h#L629-L687), please document them.

They're self documenting.

If you can't work out what each function does, crypto libraries aren't for you...
@GrayHatter Everything that is in tox.h aka. THE public API **needs** to be documented. e.e

Per IRC; no, that's stupid, and there's nothing that says that. 

And to quote myself...

> If you can't work out what each function does, crypto libraries aren't for you...
These are all generated declarations. I'll add some code to apidsl to generate documentation for them.
Didn't get to it. Apidsl is now dead. At some point we'll have apidsl v2 and generated documentation for all those things.
